						<div class="postbody">Kevtris got a lot of people's hopes up with his <a href="http://tripoint.org/kevtris/Projects/console/" class="postlink">FPGA NES</a>, but it looked like hardware manufacturing issues would keep the project from ever seeing a public release.  Then there was the One Chip MSX, a FPGA based console that also seemed very promising... yet it didn't seem to go anywhere.
<br />
<br />Well, I got the following email this morning, which makes it seem as though the One Chip MSX will finally get released!  While many people have released NES emulators for Windows, etc, is there any chance that we will see NES emulators released for the One Chip MSX?
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Bazix is pleased to announce we will soon start taking orders on a brand new One Chip MSX. On our website, we have published several pictures, new specifications and an updated FAQ on this FPGA-based computer. To sum up the most essential improvements: The One Chip MSX now is MSX2 compatible, comes with two MSX cartridge slots, two USB ports and is delivered in a stylish blue-transparent casing. <br /><br />At our website you can have a more detailed look at the new One Chip MSX, which is expected to go into production late 2006 or early 2007. As you have shown interest in the One Chip MSX in the past, and as the first batch of One Chip MSX computers will only be available on a limited offer, we invite you to join our new One Chip MSX newsletter. <br /><br />People subscribed to this newsletter will be the first to know when we start taking orders on the One Chip MSX. If you want to make sure you don't miss out on this unique opportunity we suggest you subscribe yourself as well. <br /><br />Thanks in advance, <br /><br />Bazix VOF<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.bazix.nl/onechipmsx.html">http://www.bazix.nl/onechipmsx.html</a><!-- m --><br /></div>
<br />
<br />There is also a little more info <a href="http://www.msx.org/Bazix-reveal-further-One-Chip-MSX-details-and-newsletter.newspost3891.html" class="postlink">at MSX.org</a>.</div>

