						<div class="postbody">blargg's work on NTSC emulation for the NES showed that many games have graphics that look better under NTSC emulation, due to the way it blends various colors and pixel patterns.  This isn't surprising as most Famicom/NES game developers designed the art for their game taking into consideration that kind of video distortion.
<br />
<br />How hard would it be to make your FPGA console support such a feature, so that taking a screen capture of NES games running on your FPGA NES and a real NES using a TV-tuner card produces visually identical screenshots?</div>

